%p
  Vigenere Cipher

%p 
  This cipher substitutes each character in a plaintext string with a character from a key based on its position in the Vigenere square (shown below).
  If length(plaintext) > length(key), the key repeats until the end of the plaintext. Example below:
  
%p 
  Plaintext: ATTACKATDAWN
%p 
  Key: LEMONLEMONLE
%p
  Ciphertext: LXFOPVEFRNHR

%p
  =image_tag "vsquare.jpg"
  

